Perfect! Now I can see the issue. The interface name has a typo (`CapturesArgumensFromInvocation` instead of `CapturesArgumentsFromInvocation`), and the `InvocationMatcher.java` class implements this interface. However, looking at the test `shouldMatchCaptureArgumentsWhenArgsCountDoesNOTMatch`, the problem appears to be when the number of arguments doesn't match the number of matchers in the `captureArgumentsFrom` method.

Looking at the `captureArgumentsFrom` method in `InvocationMatcher.java`:

```java
public void captureArgumentsFrom(Invocation i) {
    int k = 0;
    for (Matcher m : matchers) {
        if (m instanceof CapturesArguments) {
            ((CapturesArguments) m).captureFrom(i.getArguments()[k]);
        }
        k++;
    }
}
```

The issue is that if the number of matchers is greater than the number of arguments in the invocation, accessing `i.getArguments()[k]` will cause an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException.

Let me also check if there's a correct interface name somewhere:

